## Summary

Created the Grammar Learning feature with two files:

### `src/features/grammar/GrammarLearning.tsx`
Main component with three tabs:
- **Topics** — Browse, search, filter, sort grammar notes with CRUD (create/edit/delete/status change). Stats cards show total, mastered, reviewing, weak counts. Detail modal shows full explanation, examples, mistakes, corrections.
- **Exercises** — Grid of 20 grammar topics with exercise counts. Select any topic to start practice (10 seed exercises per topic). AI generate button creates 5 custom exercises via user API key.
- **Weaknesses** — Lists topics with most mistakes, saved grammar mistakes from exercises with ability to mark as resolved. Shows status indicators (new/reviewed/resolved).

### `src/features/grammar/components/Exercise.tsx`
Interactive exercise component supporting 4 question types:
- Multiple choice (A/B/C/D)
- Gap-fill (text input)
- True/False (two-button toggle)
- Error correction (textarea)

Features: progress bar, answer checking with immediate feedback, explanation display, auto-save incorrect answers to the `mistakes` IndexedDB store, completion screen with score summary.

### Seed Data
30 seed exercises covering 10 grammar topics (Conditionals, Articles, Passive Voice, Relative Clauses, Tenses, Prepositions, Modal Verbs, Subject-Verb Agreement, Reported Speech, Comparatives, Gerunds & Infinitives, Linking Words, Quantifiers, Punctuation, Word Order).

### Validation
- TypeScript: no errors
- Build: success
- Tests: 26/26 pas
